snippet.textDisplay: Kashif Ali has a gorgeous voice with a haunting timbre, but I keep coming back to this one for Rachel. Standing away from the spotlight the entire season in the chorus line, she gets one shot at glory, and she brings it! From the first line of her solo portion, you know she's here to play. I've been a fan of her sister, Zoe, for a while, and had seen her in  her chorus portions in previous seasons as well, but had no idea she's this much of a powerhouse. Props to Shiraz Uppal for having the vision to make this musical juxtaposition, and executing it to perfection, giving both vocalists the space to shine at their game. The changeovers are spot on, the house band, although less-noticeably than some other songs -- is on fire, and the energy of the song builds up to a magnificent crescendo with Rachel fittingly hitting an incredible final note. What a song!
